-- slice 12: getEnv returns Some when a var is set.  Both oracle and native read
-- the SAME process environment, so the result is byte-identical either way: both
-- return 1 if PATH is set, both return 0 if it is stripped.  Does NOT compare
-- the value — robust against any PATH content.
main = match getEnv "PATH"
  Some v => 1
  None => 0
